  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Phase III: Investigative Reporting in China.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IMS has been working in China since 2008. The current phase of the IMS programme in China (2012-2015), seeks to advance investigative journalism and documentary filmmaking in China, both proven to be strong vehicles for furthering media freedom. The programme uses tested tools such as training and exposure to international best practices to achieve its objectives. A number of results have been achieved during the current programme phase. IMS has successfully organized study tours, trainings and international exposure in the area of investigative and environmental journalism, carried out workshops in visual and investigative journalism at universities in three provinces of China, supported implementation of a media development assessment, created awareness raising around global standards for media freedom, supported the holding of documentary film events and created networks and links between Chinese and Danish documentary film makers. IMS has also facilitated dialogue and exchange between Danish and Chinese journalism training institutions.</narrative>
  </description>
